(secondQuint)Studies of Kidney Transplant Outcome.

 This study is looking at information already collected of transplant outcomes (short, medium and long-term complications and quality of life).

 This will specifically look at: 1.

 10 year follow-up of steroid-free maintenance immunosuppression 2.

 A cross-sectional study of infection after kidney transplantation (with emphasis on infection in steroid-free recipients 3.

 An evaluation of the Delayed Graft Function (DGF) nomogram in Thymoglobulin treated recipients at the University of Minnesota.

